data.name: CoinStats Punks
data.description:
Look, CoinStats is made up of many many "non-fungible" people, so this year we've decided on a gift that shows just how irreplaceable we all are 🧡

Initially, we were overwhelmed with the task of choosing the right holiday gift for the team: CoinStats Team is so diverse and lively, there are too many hobbies, interests, and temperaments to cover. Then it dawned on up that unique as we all are, we have a general taste for freedom, innovation, and open-mindedness that unites us. That's why this year, we at CoinStats decided to go with gifts that reflect this contrast: We created CoinStats Punks, NFTs of our team members in the crypto punk style.

We are all pixels of a big and colorful art piece that is CoinStats. And as it goes, the whole is much bigger than the sum of its parts. Happy holidays, keep the cyber-punk in you alive this coming year!

"HAIR IS OUR CROWN. OUR PRIDE, HISTORY, OUR EXPRESSION. YOU CAN’T TAKE THAT AWAY FROM US NO MORE. WE’LL WEAR IT WITH JOY AND CARE FOR IT WITH LOVE. "
I noticed how magical and powerful was always the ritual of haircare. Setting the mood, choosing one day of the week exclusively for that, buying products that were safe, shaping the hairstyle and the most important: loving the process. I connected with more women that felt the same, it was a common denominator when talking about natural hair. All those conversations inspired me to create this project. Capturing this moment in the way I perceived it. Women, in their power, brushing their hair and feeling themselves. 

We are all deserving of love. Let the most important love flow, self-love. Love is the purpose, and I’m hoping you connect with this and feel inspire to go down the road of putting yourself first and loving who you were, who you are, and who you will be.

data.name: Confecta by Nick Kuder
data.description:
Confecta is a subtle visual game, played on a 4 x 4 grid of dots, that celebrates the pleasure of color.

It explores variations of simple forms and unique color combinations within the tight formal constraints of Contecta's system.

The series was created in 2022 using a hybrid of generative and procedural processes by Nick Kuder, an Associate Professor of art, graphic designer, and visual artist.

The collection consists of 100 unique works. Each piece is named in honor of an artist, designer, or scientist who contributed to the study of color through their work — including some who were directly significant in helping shape Kuder's own development as an artist and designer.

While traveling through many galaxies, 1,000 Cosmic Ducks experienced a spacecraft failure which led them to crash into the toxic wastelands. With no access to communication devices, they fought their way through the wastelands with little success.

1 Mutant Duck Will Unlock 1 Mutant VX Duck for Sandbox

Holding a Mutant Duck will grant you access to free claims and airdrops of Cosmic Items 

Terms of Use: https://cosmic-labs.io/#/termsofuse

“A particular order can be found in deepest space, in our oceans and forests, and in all living things, including ourselves – a unified code producing endless variation.  Gravity and cosmic winds shape star-forming nebulas into coral-like forms.  Flowers self-organize in radial symmetry with signals hidden from the human eye.  Stars are birthed, explode, collapse, and are reborn.  Invertebrates move on the tides of oceans, signaling with ever-changing bioluminescence.  Light bends time as events unfold in our own lives.” 

Cosmic Reef reflects on the ordered randomness in nature, capable of producing beauty and symmetry.  The individual works begin with a simple geometry that becomes more complex through composed dynamic layers, each born of a combination of human control and computational chance.  

Leo Villareal creates intricate sculptures that speak to the underlying rules and structures of systems for both gallery and public settings.  He is interested in exploring ways to express this through base units such as pixels and binary code.  Villareal is most known for two monumental public artworks: The Bay Lights, a site-specific light sculpture that occupies the entire western span of the San Francisco-Oakland Bay Bridge, and Illuminated River, a series of generative light sculptures installed on nine bridges over the River Thames in London.

CONTROLS:

“Z”: Journey along the Z-axis   

Cosmic Reef is graphics intensive & requires a WebGL2-enabled browser.
